1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:12,200
♪

2
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:15,070
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:15,070 --> 00:01:33,210
♪

4
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:38,000
♪

5
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,290
Thanks to Kenshin,
my life was spared

6
00:01:39,290 --> 00:01:41,240
by the Sea Dragon's captain,

7
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:44,030
a mysterious woman named Shura.

8
00:01:44,030 --> 00:01:45,030
(thunder)

9
00:01:45,030 --> 00:01:47,130
Kenshin fought to
protect me from the pirates,

10
00:01:47,130 --> 00:01:50,110
but a poison dart
proved to be his undoing.

11
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:54,060
The pirates were
going to kidnap me.

12
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:56,010
Kenshin, what's wrong?

13
00:01:56,010 --> 00:01:58,280
But Kenshin talked Shura
into letting him take my place.

14
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:00,240
Take care of Kori!

15
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:02,290
♪

16
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:05,250
I love you, Kenshin!

17
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:10,120
♪

18
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:26,280
Oh...

19
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:33,260
Awake at last, I see.

20
00:02:35,210 --> 00:02:37,290
You were out cold for
quite a while, my friend,

21
00:02:37,290 --> 00:02:40,250
but then that was
a strong dose of poison you got.

22
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:47,080
Shura, it is almost time.

23
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,130
All right, Iwazo.

24
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:52,120
All hands.

25
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,240
We're almost home.

26
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:55,150
Prepare to dock and go ashore.

27
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:57,120
(cheering)

28
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:06,130
Yeah, we took
everything Mr. Yohi had,

29
00:03:06,130 --> 00:03:07,260
but it's still small potatoes.

30
00:03:07,260 --> 00:03:08,280
We need a big haul.

31
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:11,060
What's our next target?

32
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:14,010
How about that copper
mining village near Nagoya?

33
00:03:14,010 --> 00:03:15,230
Yeah, that's a good idea.

34
00:03:15,230 --> 00:03:17,050
There's just
women and kids there.

35
00:03:17,050 --> 00:03:19,000
The place isn't defended at all.

36
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,030
Oh yeah, easy pickin's,

37
00:03:21,030 --> 00:03:23,030
and besides, with
all those women around,

38
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:24,020
why, we could...

39
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:25,240
Forget it, we're not
just a bunch of thugs

40
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:28,020
who go around beating up
women and children.

41
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:32,180
Have you forgotten who we are?

42
00:03:32,180 --> 00:03:33,260
We were poor once.

43
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:36,270
My father taught you
to be worthy survivors.

44
00:03:36,270 --> 00:03:40,000
Cowards and crooks like Yohi
deserve what they get from us,

45
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,240
and there's plenty like him
to keep us fat and sassy.

46
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,230
I don't want to hear
any more talk out of you

47
00:03:44,230 --> 00:03:47,070
about attacking that
little mining town.

48
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:50,180
Now I want you all to go rest
up for the next real battle.

49
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:52,150
(clapping)

50
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:59,150
Shura, you know what?

51
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:01,240
I think that our hostage friend
deserves a little more attention

52
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,010
than we've been giving him.

53
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:05,080
After all, shore leave usually
includes a little recreation,

54
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,090
doesn't it?

55
00:04:06,090 --> 00:04:07,180
♪

56
00:04:07,180 --> 00:04:09,240
Maybe some harmless
amusement like...

57
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,040
chopping up a captive.

58
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:14,020
How about startin'
with this one?

59
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,070
There ain't much to him,

60
00:04:15,070 --> 00:04:18,070
but we can busy ourselves
for a little while at least.

61
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:19,230
♪

62
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:22,060
I think I'll just
finish him up alone.

63
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:23,270
♪

64
00:04:23,270 --> 00:04:26,100
The only question is
where to begin cuttin'.

65
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,120
At the hands or the feet...

66
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:30,030
(grunting)

67
00:04:30,030 --> 00:04:31,240
♪

68
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,210
You had better
change your tune, Geki,

69
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:36,040
or prepare yourself
to take me on.

70
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:38,050
♪

71
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:41,090
(grunting)

72
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:46,090
Hey, listen up, all of you.

73
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:48,240
I'll take care of
executing this guy.

74
00:04:48,240 --> 00:04:50,230
Gather up your
belongings and go home.

75
00:04:50,230 --> 00:04:51,210
Shura.

76
00:04:51,210 --> 00:04:52,250
-What?
-We've been talking,

77
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:54,070
and some of the men
aren't really happy

78
00:04:54,070 --> 00:04:56,100
with that arrangement.

79
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,150
Hey, listen.

80
00:04:57,150 --> 00:05:00,160
Have you decided to start
questioning my orders now?

81
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:01,140
Answer me.

82
00:05:03,180 --> 00:05:04,260
Stop it, both of you.

83
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:05,130
Huh?

84
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:08,010
Everybody go on home.

85
00:05:08,010 --> 00:05:09,250
But, you know,
she is the captain.

86
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:12,010
Let her take care
of it in her own way.

87
00:05:12,010 --> 00:05:13,010
Come on, boys.

88
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:21,010
Huh, she's startin' to annoy me.

89
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:24,030
Just because her father
was captain before her...

90
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:25,230
Aye, orderin' us
around like that.

91
00:05:34,210 --> 00:05:36,210
Bring me the prisoner's sword.

92
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:40,120
Thanks a lot, kid.

93
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,210
Now you go on home.

94
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:48,040
This is a job
I have to do myself.

95
00:05:48,040 --> 00:05:51,230
Let my assault be noble
and therefore worthy.

96
00:05:51,230 --> 00:05:53,010
Why didn't you kill me?

97
00:05:56,220 --> 00:05:58,040
You could have easily,

98
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:00,270
and we both know it.

99
00:06:00,270 --> 00:06:03,020
But you chose not
to finish me off.

100
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:07,260
Ah!

101
00:06:10,030 --> 00:06:11,230
Why?

102
00:06:11,230 --> 00:06:13,180
You could have easily beaten me,

103
00:06:13,180 --> 00:06:14,270
but you did not.

104
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,150
Fight me now.

105
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:28,120
Go on!

106
00:06:30,140 --> 00:06:32,000
What?

107
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,180
What are you grinning at?

108
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:35,010
Forgive me.

109
00:06:35,010 --> 00:06:37,110
For some reason,
a thought just occurred to me.

110
00:06:37,110 --> 00:06:40,010
If only we could have met as
friends instead of adversaries,

111
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:42,240
I would have preferred that.

112
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:44,270
How odd that fate
should bring us together

113
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:47,150
only to be enemies.

114
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:50,130
I guess you'd call this
one of the ironies of life.

115
00:06:50,130 --> 00:06:52,210
♪

116
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:54,240
Take your sword and fight me.

117
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:58,210
♪

118
00:06:58,210 --> 00:07:00,050
Pick it up and fight!

119
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:06,260
♪

120
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:08,000
No, Shura.

121
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,130
♪

122
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:10,220
Why not?

123
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:13,210
♪

124
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:16,080
Because you saved
my friend Kori's life.

125
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:18,250
To repay you,

126
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:20,280
I now offer you my life.

127
00:07:20,280 --> 00:07:23,070
♪

128
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:25,020
(angry grunt)

129
00:07:25,020 --> 00:07:26,110
Huh?

130
00:07:26,110 --> 00:07:31,070
♪

131
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:33,070
(angry grunt)

132
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:39,160
♪

133
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:41,200
(grunting)

134
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:51,040
(grunting)

135
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:03,250
(gasps)

136
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:07,030
Hm.

137
00:08:08,170 --> 00:08:10,290
Maybe I'll feel like
killing you tomorrow.

138
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:16,070
Sarujiro, take him up
to the clearing on the cliff.

139
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:19,080
Make sure he's secured.

140
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,110
Take charge of these.

141
00:08:20,110 --> 00:08:21,220
Guard 'em well.

142
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:23,260
I want you to watch
the prisoner tonight.

143
00:08:23,260 --> 00:08:24,240
Mm-hm.

144
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,290
Don't let him out of
your sight for a moment.

145
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:45,100
I have a feeling that Kori
is looking up at the moon

146
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,270
and wondering where I am.

147
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:50,100
I've got to escape somehow.

148
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:55,210
♪

149
00:08:55,210 --> 00:08:58,090
Sarujiro, you're a good guard.

150
00:08:58,090 --> 00:09:00,120
You take your work
pretty seriously, don't you?

151
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,000
Hm.

152
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,060
So, does Captain Shura
treat you well?

153
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,290
Huh?

154
00:09:05,290 --> 00:09:07,020
Mm-hm.

155
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:10,230
Well, it's obvious
that she cares about you.

156
00:09:10,230 --> 00:09:11,230
You like her too?

157
00:09:11,230 --> 00:09:13,240
Mm-hm.

158
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,180
(gasps)

159
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:16,220
Mm.

160
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:18,040
Oh.

161
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,170
(laughs)

162
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:40,010
♪

163
00:09:40,010 --> 00:09:41,060
(footsteps)

164
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:43,050
Shura, I want to talk to you.

165
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:48,040
Ginjo, I thought you went home.

166
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:49,170
What is it now?

167
00:09:49,170 --> 00:09:51,030
What's so important?

168
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:52,060
Hey, I'm just curious.

169
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:53,220
So why didn't you kill him?

170
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:57,200
Don't tell me that you might be
falling for that skinny reject.

171
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,150
What?

172
00:09:58,150 --> 00:10:00,010
You've gotta be kidding.

173
00:10:00,010 --> 00:10:01,250
Why would I do that?

174
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,110
Why not?

175
00:10:02,110 --> 00:10:03,140
You could have.

176
00:10:03,140 --> 00:10:05,040
After all, you're still a lady.

177
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,010
Huh?

178
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:08,140
I never even thought
of myself as female.

179
00:10:08,140 --> 00:10:10,230
Hold it right there, princess.

180
00:10:10,230 --> 00:10:12,040
You're a girl, all right.

181
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:15,040
All you need is to spend a
little time with a man like me.

182
00:10:16,230 --> 00:10:18,200
(grunts)

183
00:10:20,070 --> 00:10:22,080
Ha.

184
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,050
(grunting)

185
00:10:26,210 --> 00:10:28,160
Ginjo, I swear I'm
going to kill you

186
00:10:28,160 --> 00:10:30,230
if you ever touch
me like that again.

187
00:10:30,230 --> 00:10:33,200
You're a member of
the crew and nothing more.

188
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:36,180
I am the captain
of the Sea Dragon.

189
00:10:36,180 --> 00:10:38,240
Pig.

190
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,210
(winces)

191
00:10:43,130 --> 00:10:46,080
You're gonna
freakin' regret that.

192
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:48,160
Ginjo, I could have
told you that little bitch

193
00:10:48,160 --> 00:10:49,210
was a handful.

194
00:10:51,090 --> 00:10:53,052
Hey, forget about it.

195
00:10:53,052 --> 00:10:54,131
Come with me.

196
00:10:54,131 --> 00:10:55,030
I got somethin' to show ya

197
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:57,120
that'll pick
your spirits right up.

198
00:10:57,120 --> 00:11:00,030
♪

199
00:11:00,030 --> 00:11:02,180
I figured we could make
some money with the silk

200
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:04,160
we got from Yohi.

201
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:07,000
But some of the crates
didn't feel like silk,

202
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,010
so I dug around,
and guess what I found

203
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:11,000
underneath in one of 'em?

204
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,130
So Mr. Yohi deals in opium.

205
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,130
And there's more.

206
00:11:14,130 --> 00:11:16,030
Look under that.

207
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:19,040
I think maybe we've stumbled
into that big haul you wanted.

208
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:20,220
I believe you're
right, my friend.

209
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:22,160
This will make us wealthy.

210
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,110
This is only one
shipment of the stuff.

211
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:27,030
There must be a whole lot
more wherever this came from.

212
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:29,100
♪

213
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:31,130
I'll pay a visit to Yohi,

214
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:34,210
and I think life is about to
change for our beloved captain.

215
00:11:41,290 --> 00:11:44,010
You know, the best thing
about drinking alone

216
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:45,170
is you get more to drink.

217
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:46,190
(laughs)

218
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:48,050
There's no more in this one.

219
00:11:48,050 --> 00:11:49,040
This one's empty.

220
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,260
I know there's some
more in one of these.

221
00:11:50,260 --> 00:11:52,200
Yep, it's this one, I think.

222
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,190
They stole 20 pounds of opium

223
00:11:54,190 --> 00:11:56,080
and all those rifles from me.

224
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,250
Oh boy.

225
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,020
Ah!

226
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:00,971
Why did those pirates have to
pick on me anyway, the chumps!

227
00:12:00,971 --> 00:12:01,791
Yohi!

228
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:02,290
Ah!

229
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:04,280
Where are you?

230
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:06,220
I'm in here.

231
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:08,060
♪

232
00:12:08,060 --> 00:12:09,290
That voice sounds familiar.

233
00:12:09,290 --> 00:12:11,030
Ah!

234
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:12,030
♪

235
00:12:12,030 --> 00:12:13,200
Ah...

236
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,150
(trembling)

237
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:16,060
I'm so glad I
caught you at home.

238
00:12:16,060 --> 00:12:19,030
We have a lot to
talk about, partner.

239
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,010
I'm disappointed.

240
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:22,080
You don't look
very happy to see me.

241
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:24,050
Oh, why, yes, of--no.

242
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:26,000
I would like you to
continue your trafficking

243
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:28,210
in opium and
firearms, old friend.

244
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:31,020
I'm even gonna help.

245
00:12:31,020 --> 00:12:33,150
Now you're probably wondering
what I get out of this deal,

246
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:34,070
aren't ya?

247
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:35,032
Say yes.

248
00:12:35,032 --> 00:12:36,160
Uh huh, uh huh.

249
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:38,040
I knew you were gonna say that.

250
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:41,010
Okay now, here's what
you're gonna do for me.

251
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:42,240
♪

252
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:46,290
I know you're worried, Kori,
and I think about it too,

253
00:12:46,290 --> 00:12:49,130
but you can't let it
spoil your appetite.

254
00:12:49,130 --> 00:12:50,090
You gotta eat.

255
00:12:50,090 --> 00:12:51,200
Keep up your strength.

256
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:54,100
But it's all my fault
that he's on that ship.

257
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:56,050
If I hadn't got
so upset about money,

258
00:12:56,050 --> 00:12:58,080
Kenshin would be
here having supper.

259
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:02,250
(gargling)

260
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:04,190
(muffled yelp)

261
00:13:04,190 --> 00:13:06,280
(dazed muttering)

262
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,290
Sano, I'll thank you
not to gargle sake

263
00:13:08,290 --> 00:13:10,250
while I'm worrying.

264
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:13,010
But, Kori, don't you see
you're not gonna help Kenshin

265
00:13:13,010 --> 00:13:15,110
by worrying and starving
yourself like this?

266
00:13:15,110 --> 00:13:17,020
Besides, what good
is a dead hostage?

267
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:18,210
They gotta feed him.

268
00:13:18,210 --> 00:13:20,170
To tell you the truth,
I think he jumped into it

269
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:22,250
because he was lookin' for
a little change of scenery,

270
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,280
some excitement.

271
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:25,030
He's like that.

272
00:13:25,030 --> 00:13:26,290
I feel responsible.

273
00:13:26,290 --> 00:13:28,290
Kenshin knew what
he was getting into.

274
00:13:28,290 --> 00:13:31,050
Anyway, tomorrow
something's bound to turn up.

275
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:32,130
Hey guys!

276
00:13:32,130 --> 00:13:35,110
Come on, I think I got a lead
where they've taken Kenshin.

277
00:13:35,110 --> 00:13:37,050
They were comin'
out of Yohi's place.

278
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:38,070
Who was?

279
00:13:38,070 --> 00:13:40,110
Pirates, who do
you think I meant?

280
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:42,110
(grunting)

281
00:13:42,110 --> 00:13:50,100
♪

282
00:13:50,100 --> 00:13:52,160
Yep, those are
the pirates of the Sea Dragon.

283
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:54,000
♪

284
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,130
Anybody got an idea?

285
00:13:55,130 --> 00:13:56,220
The only way to find Kenshin

286
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:58,110
is to follow them
back to their ship.

287
00:13:58,110 --> 00:13:59,240
That won't be
a walk in the park.

288
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,180
-Are you up to it?
-Mm-hm.

289
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:04,110
Then I guess we've gotta go
and find ourselves a boat.

290
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:05,140
Mm-hm.

291
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:10,100
♪

292
00:14:27,190 --> 00:14:29,240
Yohi really came through.

293
00:14:29,240 --> 00:14:31,270
Now that Yohi's
our business partner,

294
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:33,080
we'll be able to
get the provisions

295
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,130
a big ship like
this really needs.

296
00:14:35,130 --> 00:14:37,060
Smile, Yohi.

297
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:39,070
Fellas, you'll have to
excuse our guest of honor.

298
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:41,110
He's still upset over
a shipment of his weapons

299
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:42,180
that fell into our hands.

300
00:14:42,180 --> 00:14:44,150
But we'll put them
to good use sometime.

301
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,140
Weapons?

302
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:46,170
Why didn't you tell us?

303
00:14:46,170 --> 00:14:47,130
Let's see 'em.

304
00:14:47,130 --> 00:14:49,180
Calm down, all in good time.

305
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:51,170
I wanted it to be a surprise.

306
00:14:51,170 --> 00:14:52,060
See?

307
00:14:52,060 --> 00:14:53,230
Look at those.

308
00:14:53,230 --> 00:14:56,020
With these, nobody
can stand up to us.

309
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,280
New lever action
repeater rifles,

310
00:14:57,280 --> 00:15:00,050
enough of 'em to arm
every man on the ship.

311
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:01,130
And as if that weren't enough,

312
00:15:01,130 --> 00:15:04,060
our pal Yohi here is gonna
buy us a brand new boat,

313
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:05,240
isn't that right, pal?

314
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,020
And he's gonna buy it for us

315
00:15:07,020 --> 00:15:09,130
with the profits from
selling all that opium.

316
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:12,070
But there's still a fly
in the ointment, Ginjo.

317
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,140
(sips)

318
00:15:16,140 --> 00:15:19,000
Yeah, a fly by
the name of Shura.

319
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,250
Yeah, what about her?

320
00:15:20,250 --> 00:15:23,070
So how does Shura
figure into these plans,

321
00:15:23,070 --> 00:15:24,190
or does she?

322
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:29,010
You bet your hat she does.

323
00:15:29,010 --> 00:15:31,080
But since Shura doesn't
like our choice of targets,

324
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:33,120
I plan to eliminate her.

325
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,090
(screams)

326
00:15:36,130 --> 00:15:37,100
(slam)

327
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,020
Hm?

328
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,240
Huh?

329
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:51,160
Hm.

330
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:53,180
It's just a little bitty rodent.

331
00:15:53,180 --> 00:15:56,250
A little bitty rodent,
ain't that cute.

332
00:15:56,250 --> 00:16:00,130
♪

333
00:16:00,130 --> 00:16:02,040
Yeah, a rat.

334
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:09,150
(soft snoring)

335
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:14,280
If I could only have one wish,

336
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:17,030
it would be to be
back at the Kamiya dojo

337
00:16:17,030 --> 00:16:18,250
with all my friends.

338
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:21,040
I hope they're safe and sound.

339
00:16:21,040 --> 00:16:24,020
I trust Kori has
recovered from her injuries.

340
00:16:24,020 --> 00:16:26,080
(footsteps approaching)

341
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:31,230
♪

342
00:16:31,230 --> 00:16:32,230
Huh?

343
00:16:32,230 --> 00:16:41,090
♪

344
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:52,040
It certainly is
a beautiful night.

345
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:54,020
Hey, listen.

346
00:16:54,020 --> 00:16:55,150
Tell me something.

347
00:16:55,150 --> 00:16:57,080
What is it you want to ask?

348
00:16:57,080 --> 00:17:00,060
This--this friend of yours,

349
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:02,120
the girl you call Kori?

350
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:04,220
I would like you to
tell me something about her.

351
00:17:04,220 --> 00:17:06,020
But what's the reason you ask?

352
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:07,200
I want to know!

353
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,060
Humor me.

354
00:17:09,060 --> 00:17:11,050
Tell me what it is
that makes that person

355
00:17:11,050 --> 00:17:14,230
someone that you would
give up everything for.

356
00:17:14,230 --> 00:17:16,220
Please enlighten me.

357
00:17:16,220 --> 00:17:18,180
I would really like to know.

358
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:22,020
♪

359
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:24,160
What shall I tell
you about her?

360
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:27,060
My friend Kori
has enormous courage.

361
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:29,130
She's generous
and compassionate,

362
00:17:29,130 --> 00:17:32,130
and she has no idea
how special she really is.

363
00:17:32,130 --> 00:17:35,120
She's far better at caring
for others than for herself.

364
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:37,050
♪

365
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:41,040
And deep inside,
she's very lonely.

366
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:42,130
Now that I think about it,

367
00:17:42,130 --> 00:17:44,010
you remind me of
her a little bit.

368
00:17:44,010 --> 00:17:44,831
Can you cook?

369
00:17:44,831 --> 00:17:46,010
(gasps)

370
00:17:46,010 --> 00:17:47,080
Huh?

371
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:49,190
You don't know me well enough.

372
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:51,190
(soft snoring)

373
00:17:51,190 --> 00:18:02,170
♪

374
00:18:02,170 --> 00:18:05,130
Then please tell me
about your background, Shura.

375
00:18:05,130 --> 00:18:07,150
Maybe then I'd
understand you better.

376
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:09,040
I'd really like to know.

377
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:11,240
♪

378
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:13,060
When I was a child,

379
00:18:13,060 --> 00:18:15,140
this village was hideously poor.

380
00:18:15,140 --> 00:18:17,130
Rather than see us
all starve to death,

381
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:20,130
my father stole from
the provincial robber barons.

382
00:18:20,130 --> 00:18:22,120
♪

383
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:25,090
My father did what he had
to to keep us all alive.

384
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:26,290
♪

385
00:18:26,290 --> 00:18:30,210
The children he fed are
the crew that serve under me.

386
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:33,200
He was a thief with
an iron code of honor.

387
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:36,100
♪

388
00:18:43,140 --> 00:18:45,270
Is it set?

389
00:18:45,270 --> 00:18:48,030
I'm gonna miss this old tub.

390
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,000
(snickering)

391
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:58,020
Why, those lousy pirates--huh?

392
00:18:58,020 --> 00:19:00,170
Sano, you know we've got to
get out of here right away.

393
00:19:00,170 --> 00:19:01,290
I think they knew we were here.

394
00:19:01,290 --> 00:19:04,050
Actually, Kori, I think
we need to jump off this ship

395
00:19:04,050 --> 00:19:05,020
right away.

396
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:07,040
But why should we abandon ship?

397
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,120
Well, let's just
say I have a feeling.

398
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:12,120
♪

399
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,030
This way.

400
00:19:14,030 --> 00:19:15,270
No, stop.

401
00:19:15,270 --> 00:19:17,230
I can smell something burning.

402
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:19,150
♪

403
00:19:19,150 --> 00:19:20,140
Gunpowder!

404
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:21,110
(explosion)

405
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:24,010
An explosion on my ship.

406
00:19:24,010 --> 00:19:26,040
Don't go down there, Shura.

407
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:27,200
Ginjo wants to take over.

408
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:29,150
Your crew just
blew up your ship.

409
00:19:29,150 --> 00:19:30,290
They would never do that.

410
00:19:30,290 --> 00:19:33,170
Your crew isn't as grateful
as you think they are.

411
00:19:33,170 --> 00:19:34,190
It isn't gratitude.

412
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:37,050
My crew counts on me
for their very survival.

413
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:39,150
They don't need you
for survival, Shura.

414
00:19:39,150 --> 00:19:40,160
(grunting)

415
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,160
And their pirate code
is the code of cutthroats.

416
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,220
Don't you understand?

417
00:19:43,220 --> 00:19:46,090
You don't know what you're
talking about, swordsman.

418
00:19:46,090 --> 00:19:47,170
As they served my father,

419
00:19:47,170 --> 00:19:49,210
my crew will
serve me to the end!

420
00:19:49,210 --> 00:19:52,080
I bet her crew will sooner
serve her to the sharks.

421
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:53,230
It's up to me.

422
00:19:53,230 --> 00:19:55,150
(grunting)

423
00:19:55,150 --> 00:19:57,090
♪

424
00:19:57,090 --> 00:19:59,250
I've just gotta break
out of these ropes.

425
00:19:59,250 --> 00:20:01,280
♪

426
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:03,010
I heard an explosion.

427
00:20:03,010 --> 00:20:04,070
What happened?

428
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:07,280
♪

429
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,170
Hey, what's the matter with you?

430
00:20:09,170 --> 00:20:11,070
Shura!

431
00:20:11,070 --> 00:20:13,070
(grunting)

432
00:20:13,070 --> 00:20:19,260
♪

433
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,270
Shura, get Sarujiro.

434
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:22,290
Did you hear me?

435
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:24,140
Shura!

436
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:25,130
Sarujiro needs you.

437
00:20:25,130 --> 00:20:26,280
You must take care of him.

438
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:27,230
Huh?

439
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:29,140
Oh, yes.

440
00:20:29,140 --> 00:20:30,220
Ya!

441
00:20:30,220 --> 00:20:32,010
(laughing)

442
00:20:32,010 --> 00:20:36,040
♪

443
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:37,250
Ya!

444
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:38,260
♪

445
00:20:38,260 --> 00:20:40,260
(grunting)

446
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:43,150
♪

447
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:46,290
Ah, quit foolin' around, boys.

448
00:20:46,290 --> 00:20:49,110
Hey, I mean, if you
want to get rid of him,

449
00:20:49,110 --> 00:20:50,070
blast him.

450
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:52,030
Uh, but, men...

451
00:20:52,030 --> 00:20:53,090
♪

452
00:20:53,090 --> 00:20:54,010
(gunshot)

453
00:20:54,010 --> 00:20:55,240
(grunts)

454
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:58,210
♪

455
00:20:58,210 --> 00:20:59,190
Shura!

456
00:20:59,190 --> 00:21:02,060
(gunshots)

457
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:04,060
(panting)

458
00:21:04,060 --> 00:21:08,210
♪

459
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:10,250
Well, would you
look at that now?

460
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:13,030
♪

461
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:18,250
Hm.

462
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:20,000
Well, how 'bout that?

463
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,230
We got two pests
out of the way

464
00:21:21,230 --> 00:21:23,050
at the same time.

465
00:21:23,050 --> 00:21:25,050
(laughing)

466
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:27,020
(whimpering)

467
00:21:29,090 --> 00:21:31,060
(roar of waterfalls)

468
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:39,060
♪

469
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:42,060
(singing in foreign language)

470
00:21:42,060 --> 00:23:08,030
♪

471
00:23:09,060 --> 00:23:11,290
♪

